  "text": "i.e. the hourly electricity consumption, Q t is equal to the summation over N devices of the power demand of each device, q j in state s, where s is a function of the time period of the day, T, the prior state, s-1, and the matrix of transition probabilities, P. For an office computer (including the monitor), the power demand q has been assumed to be 5 W in the 'Off' state, 65 W in the 'Low' state and 100 W in the 'On' state [CITATION_1] .",
